/**
 * Calculates the n-th element in the Tribonacci sequence.
 * This sequence is similar to Fibonacci but starts with three predefined values and each next number
 * is a sum of the three preceding ones.
 * 
 * @param {number} n - The position in the sequence to return.
 * @param {Array<number>} [sequence=[0, 1, 1]] - The starting values of the Tribonacci sequence.
 * @return {number} The n-th element in the Tribonacci sequence.
 */
function tribonacci(n, sequence = [0, 1, 1]) {
    if (n < sequence.length) return sequence[n];

    for (let i = 3; i <= n; i++) {
        sequence[i] = sequence[i - 1] + sequence[i - 2] + sequence[i - 3];
    }

    return sequence[n];
}

// Example usage
console.log(tribonacci(24)); // Outputs the 24th element in the Tribonacci sequence
```

This solution introduces a function `tribonacci` that calculates the n-th element in the Tribonacci sequence. It initializes a base sequence with the first three numbers `[0, 1, 1]` and iteratively calculates subsequent numbers until the n-th position is reached. This approach is efficient and avoids the exponential time complexity of a naive recursive solution, allowing for the computation of quite large sequence indices in a reasonable time frame.

